Text: Commoners and aristocrats, aren't we humans at the end of the day? Come this way if you want to live!

Name: Commoner
Text: Okay, I got it!

Name: Lee
Text: We're safe now.

Name: Liv
Text: That's great...

Name: Lucia
Text: We'd better leave once we've planned our next step.

Name: System
Text: (Akdilek Record)

Name: System
Text: This train is refitted with the Central Purification Filter designs of the City Series of 020, 030, and 050.

Name: System
Text: But the truth is, the filter is not capable of supporting the whole train.

Name: System
Text: Therefore, after the completion of all works, all carriages will be classified and, superior races will be separated from the inferior ones.

Name: System
Text: Like Babylonia, we will keep hope alive.

Name: Lucia
Text: Sophia, enemy signals come from there!

Name: Sophia
Text: There's a ladder ahead on the train roof.

Name: Lee
Text: If we'd been allowed to do our work earlier, none of this would've happened.

Name: Lee
Text: Message from the command center... Reinforcements?

Name: Liv
Text: Move now, Commandant.

Name: Lee
Text: Wait, something falling down!

Name: Sophia
Text: No more obstacles. I have to reach Changyu quickly.

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's go, Commandant!

Name: Lucia
Text: Is it... a letter?

Name: Construct
Text: My name... It no longer matters. I thought I could have gotten through this train and completed the mission.

Name: Construct
Text: But in the end, I was still a fool. I was classified as a pariah, a slave.

Name: Construct
Text: If we don't act... The Ascendants will...

Name: Construct
Text: I'm already drained... So...!

Name: Construct
Text: Please be careful of... a thing called "Lullaby".

Name: Lee
Text: The kid from Akdilek... seems to be severely wounded.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Bring it on!

Name: Lucia
Text: We're able to close in on the enemies at this rate.

Name: Liv
Text: Wait, Lucia, Lee. The Heterozygote's reaction...

Name: Lucia
Text: Ugh!

Name: Liv
Text: Lucia! Lee!

Name: Liv
Text: Commandant, Lucia and Lee have fallen off the train!

Name: Liv
Text: If we get off the train now, those people might...

Name: Liv
Text: The radar doesn't lose Lucia and Lee's signals...

Name: Liv
Text: At this rate... Let's go back to the carriage first and wait for Lucia and Lee, Commandant.

Name: Corrupted
Text: Urgh—!

Name: Bianca
Text: My presence has been exposed...

Name: Bianca
Text: It's been a long time since I used this frame.

Name: Bianca
Text: Hope I can still handle it.

Name: Bianca
Text: The gate operating system has been damaged a bit.

Name: Bianca
Text: We can find the parts from the nearby remains to repair it...

Name: Bianca
Text: Only uncorrupted parts can be used to fix the gate.

Name: Bianca
Text: There are many Corrupted nearby. Any mistakes will alert them. Be careful.

Name: Bianca
Text: ...Still works.

Name: Bianca
Text: Everything seems to have remained the same.

Name: Bianca
Text: Then, I only have to wait on the second floor.

Name: Bianca
Text: Finally, the upper floor... Should be able to see the train soon.

Name: Bianca
Text: We need to move fast.

Name: Bianca
Text: It's Gronin Station notice...

Name: Bianca
Text: ...This station will cease operations once the construction of Gestalt's new circuit network is completed.

Name: Bianca
Text: All gates will be closed from today onwards, and the staff will be transported out of this place once their IDs are deleted.

Name: Bianca
Text: But those track maintenance machines, whether they are personal property or not, are not allowed to be taken away from this station.

Name: Bianca
Text: Afterward, (an unclear name) will take over the station.

Name: Bianca
Text: This is the Gestalt Order No. 202 approved by the World Government. Please keep calm and follow the order.

Name: Bianca
Text: The train will pass through here soon enough.

Name: Bianca
Text: But the gate has blocked the passage. We have to close it again as soon as possible.

Name: Bianca
Text: There are many Corrupted lurking around.

Name: Bianca
Text: We can't go forward if we don't deal with this.

Name: Bianca
Text: All cleared. And the next is...

Name: Lucia
Text: Bianca... Why are you here?

Name: Bianca
Text: Lucia? and that motorcycle...

Name: Lucia
Text: I found it ahead. I'm ready to go after it now.

Name: Bianca
Text: What's wrong?

Name: Lucia
Text: You're not going?

Name: Bianca
Text: (Sighs)

Name: Lucia
Text: Full speed ahead!

Name: Bianca
Text: Wait, slow down!

Name: Lucia
Text: The train runs too fast, but I can't lag behind anymore. Commandant needs me.

Name: Lucia
Text: Bianca, please shoot down the enemies in our way, otherwise we won't be able to approach the train.

Name: Bianca
Text: Target confirmed in the Hawkeye sight distance.

Name: Lucia
Text: That's good enough, Bianca. Let's jump on the train!

Name: Liv
Text: It's still moving forward. The train will stop running if the engine is corrupted, and the people will...

Name: Lucia
Text: The filter will go down if the train stops...

Name: Lee
Text: Which means arriving at the terminal earlier than expected?

Name: Sophia
Text: This isn't the train's terminal... Our train won't stop there!

Name: Liv
Text: This is—Watch out!

Name: Liv
Text: It's just like in the space station. A faint energy activity still remains within that burnt frame!

Name: Lucia
Text: Same move again? But this time...

Name: Chrome
Text: The visual designs match with the style of "Kowloong". Could it be...

Name: Kamui
Text: That's our guy! Hey, stop running!

Name: Chrome
Text: Don't be reckless, Kamui!

Name: Kamui
Text: Leader!

Name: Chrome
Text: I'll take the lead. Watch my back!

Name: Chrome
Text: ...Tsk.

Name: Chrome
Text: It shouldn't have much energy left. Should still be nearby.

Name: Chrome
Text: The Corrupted are attracted by the commotion of combat...

Name: Chrome
Text: They even have more helpers...

Name: Chrome
Text: Were they already hidden nearby under camouflage?

Name: Chrome
Text: Gotcha!

Name: Kamui
Text: Leader, are you alright?!

Name: Chrome
Text: It ran away.

Name: Kamui
Text: Ran away?

Name: Chrome
Text: Don't worry. I've got its info recorded.

Name: Chrome
Text: No matter where it goes, we'll be able to track it.

Name: Commandant
Text: A connection is made to a virtual M.I.N.D. of one of the guards outside.

Name: Commandant
Text: The virtual M.I.N.D. of mechanoid is more akin to a simulation of reality.

Name: Commandant
Text: Perhaps the passcode to the cabin door can be found in its memory data.

Name: Ballwheel IV
Text: Thinking circuits... Abnormal...

Name: M.I.N.D. Data 004
Text: Area under attack... Intruders are... From... Side E...

Name: Commandant
Text: Lucia, Liv, Lee. Wait for me.

Name: M.I.N.D. Data 001
Text: Type IV... Rolling out. Type I, disobeyed orders, dismantled.

Name: M.I.N.D. Data 002
Text: Cutting, isn't, performing. Want, voice, device. Want, singing.

Name: M.I.N.D. Data 003
Text: Protect, the, goods. Why, not, a, performance mission?

Name: Mysterious Voice
Text: The traps have an attack interval. Maybe you can find an opportunity to go through.

Name: Mysterious Voice
Text: The virtual M.I.N.D. is still part of the M.I.N.D., so there may be some overflowing data.

Name: Mysterious Voice
Text: Once attacked, you'll need some time to regenerate.

Name: Mysterious Voice
Text: If you find a trap impossible to pass, try destroying it with attacks.

Name: Lee
Text: So this place isn't unguarded after all. Look at those performer-bots...

Name: Lucia
Text: They're coming for us.

Name: Lucia
Text: Seems like they don't want to disturb the people in the night market.

Name: Lee
Text: They may have been ordered to ensure the market is running normally.

Name: Lee
Text: They want to direct us away from the market. Great, exactly what we want.

Name: Liv
Text: No infection detected. They're just normal mechanoids...

Name: Commandant
Text: Don't damage their core modules. Do it cleanly, then we get off the ship.

Name: Lee
Text: Okay.

Name: Lucia
Text: Commandant, please give your orders.

Name: All
Text: (Cheering)

Name: Lee
Text: The people thought we were putting on a show...

Name: Lucia
Text: Now that Commandant is back, let's get off the ship first.

Name: Lee
Text: ...They found us already. How fast.

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's run.

Name: Lee
Text: Now they're waiting ahead of us?

Name: Lucia
Text: We don't have time. We'll have to force through them...
At least let me finish!
Stop these people.

Name: Hanged Man
Text: —Item 01, please come on stage.

Name: Cheering
Text: YEEEAAAAHH—!

Name: Cheering
Text: Marvelous! This is so beautiful!

Name: Booing
Text: What a poser!

Name: Hanged Man
Text: O—Gorgeous lady—

Name: Hanged Man
Text: —Go to the surrounding stages—If you wish to win—

Name: Hanged Man
Text: Show us your strength—Good luck—

Name: Yazi
Text: I have underestimated your strength.

Name: Yazi
Text: Now, I shall conduct the final test on behalf of Leader.

Name: Chrome
Text: ...They are the puppets from the performance troupe.

Name: Chrome
Text: But there's probably more to them.

Name: Chrome
Text: Targets eliminated.

Name: Chrome
Text: Do help keep "Yazi" at bay when I get close to the stage...

Name: Chrome
Text: That person on the observation deck...

Name: Chrome
Text: As I expected, there are puppets with attack modules installed amongst the performing puppets.

Name: Yazi
Text: Do not get any closer.

Name: Yazi
Text: Master's wish will soon be realized.

Name: Yazi
Text: You're not going to interrupt...

Name: Liv
Text: Lucia, you can't move yet...

Name: Lucia
Text: I'm fine... Let me fight.

Name: Lucia
Text: Commandant, please trust me.

Name: Qu
Text: Almost there.

Name: Qu
Text: Out of my way, Gray Raven!

Name: Qu
Text: If that's the case... I shall take control over this M.I.N.D.

Name: Qu
Text: Huaxu... Give me your power now!

Name: Chrome
Text: What are they talking about...?

Name: Chrome
Text: But right now I have something more important to do...

Name: Robotic Voice
Text: ...Please be seated... The following names...

Name: Robotic Voice
Text: Will be... activated... by the Kowloong Crew...

Name: Robotic Voice
Text: ...The trade fair shall commence once the goods are ready...

Name: Chrome
Text: What's going on...?

Name: Chrome
Text: The space is shifting...

Name: Construct Guard
Text: Support here yet...?

Name: Construct Leader
Text: Divide yourselves into two teams. One'll set up the defenses while the other engages the enemies!

Name: Construct Guard
Text: More Corrupted incoming!

Name: Construct Guard
Text: Just us, against that entire horde?!

Name: Construct Leader
Text: As long as we are together, there's nothing to fear. Hold your line!

Name: Bridget
Text: Yes... We have arrived at the defense point of the civilian district.

Name: Bridget
Text: The situation isn't looking good... The Corrupted have already... Dammit! (Hangs off)

Name: Bridget
Text: Hold your line! Watch the surroundings!

Name: Construct Leader
Text: Are you the Support Force...?

Name: Bridget
Text: Yes. I'm Bridget, one of the squad leaders of the SF. Sorry, didn't expect them to come so fast.

Name: Construct Leader
Text: I'm the leader of the vanguard squad E... Thanks for your assistance!

Name: Bridget
Text: Let's get through this together!

Name: Construct Leader
Text: Jitterbombs detected. Fire!

Name: Construct Leader
Text: Jitterbombs are coming at us. Use special bullets against them!

Name: Phecda
Text: All intruders must be exterminated.

Name: Bridget
Text: These bastards! They are attacking anyone that's not one of them!

Name: Construct Leader
Text: Your assistance is much appreciated! We managed to suffer only minimum losses.

Name: Construct Leader
Text: We can defend this place a bit longer after some rest.

Name: Bridget
Text: But don't push yourselves too hard.

Name: Construct Leader
Text: Your assistance is much appreciated! We suffered some losses, but we'll be fine.

Name: Construct Leader
Text: We can still fight.

Name: Bridget
Text: The Corrupted will keep coming.

Name: Bridget
Text: I'll get you more reinforcements ASAP.

Name: Construct Leader
Text: That will be great.

Name: Bridget
Text: I'll take the wounded away for now.

Name: Bridget
Text: No way... They have all died...

Name: Bridget
Text: I couldn't even save one of them...

Name: Reinforcement
Text: Boss, the other side's also...

Name: Bridget
Text: Try to retrieve as many frames as possible. There must be something we can do.

Name: Bridget
Text: Let's retreat for now!

Name: Reinforcement
Text: Roger!

Name: α
Text: Lucia, I thought you'd grow under that Commandant.

Name: Lucia
Text: I did.

Name: α
Text: ...But not enough, Lucia!

Name: Lee
Text: My shots aren't connecting with her... Wait, could she be?!

Name: Lucia
Text: Ugh...

Name: α
Text: You take on my face. You take on my blade. You take on my voice. Yet you still speak words I've long since left behind.

Name: α
Text: You had your chance.

Name: Liv
Text: Lucia!

Name: α
Text: Now die.

Name: Liv
Text: Incoming Corrupted detected! Wait, no, they're Heteromers!

Name: Liv
Text: Commandant, we have lots of Heteromers coming in!

Name: α
Text: Lamia's work? Sloppy as always...

Name: α
Text: I'll fall back for now...

Name: Liv
Text: The Heteromers are coming!

Name: Construct Leader
Text: We got this!

Name: Construct Guard
Text: Just focus on the enemies in front of you, folks.

Name: α
Text: Very well then. Both the Corrupted and the Constructs are gone.

Name: α
Text: Nothing stands in our way now.

Name: α
Text: Don't let me down again, Lucia.

Name: Forsaken Member
Text: ...Mr. Watanabe.

Name: Watanabe
Text: Stay vigilant. These Heteromer Cubes are all potential threats.

Name: Watanabe
Text: If I'm right, there must be quite a few Corrupted around here... linked to these cubes.

Name: Watanabe
Text: They must be the remains of that gravity core... They're adapting to Earth's environment.

Name: Lee
Text: What is this place?

Name: Liv
Text: How gorgeous and well-kept.

Name: Ayla
Text: Looks like we've come to a dead end... Shall we turn back?
No, you face not a dead end.

Name: Lee
Text: Yazi... Why are you here?
No, I am not Yazi.

Name: Liv
Text: What do you mean? Who are you then?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Going back will take your precious time. So if you are after the Ascendants—

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Answer my questions, and you may pass. Of course, you are also welcome to break through with force.

Name: Ayla
Text: Um... Do you know her?

Name: Liv
Text: S-sort of...? (Dry laughter)

Name: Lee
Text: So she's controlling the passage here. Alright.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Are you ready? Let's begin...

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: The first question is...

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Here comes the second question...

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: And the third question is...

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Light and shadow are one and the same. Where the light flourishes, the shadow also prospers.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: In the courtyard there is an abundance of light, in the shadows the answer hides.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Show me the "Lightless Veranda" should you seek the truth.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: That is all. Do take your time.

Name: Ayla
Text: What does "lightless" mean...? It's so bright everywhere.

Name: Liv
Text: No. There is one place without light.

Name: Lee
Text: Commandant, please make your decision.

Name: Ayla
Text: Compared with the other verandas...

Name: Ayla
Text: This one isn't any different...

Name: Lee
Text: Not quite... Just look up...

Name: Ayla
Text: Oh...! I see...!

Name: Liv
Text: This is what differs this veranda from the others.

Name: Ayla
Text: I see... The light isn't on...

Name: Ayla
Text: Is that what "lightless" meant?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Wind flows through the void, traveling to and fro in the courtyard.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: But anchored is your answer, untouched it is by ebbs and flows.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Should you desire the truth, locate the "Chamber of Windrest".

Name: Lee
Text: She said "windrest"... Hmm...

Name: Ayla
Text: Ah, I got it! The wind must stop somewhere!

Name: Ayla
Text: Commandant, we just have to find a place without wind.

Name: Ayla
Text: I can't put it into words, but...

Name: Ayla
Text: I have a feeling that this is the place.

Name: Liv
Text: Hmm... Looking up close, the wind here is a lot weaker.

Name: Liv
Text: See, the painting is barely moving.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Causes criss-crosses with effect. That which touches this land not, therein your answer lies.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: You will find your answer in the "Pavilion of Difference".

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: That which exists here not shall lead you to the pavilion.

Name: Ayla
Text: Did she mention "difference"?

Name: Liv
Text: There are three shades of different machines. Looks like we need to find the correct answer from them...

Name: Lee
Text: One of them is different from the others. Commandant, it's very obvious, don't you think?

Name: Lee
Text: I knew it...

Name: Lee
Text: One of the illusions is different from the rest.

Name: Ayla
Text: Different? What do you mean...

Name: Liv
Text: This Heteromer unit is only seen in Asslam. It doesn't exist in this city.

Name: Liv
Text: That's the "difference" she was talking about.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Very well. Would you like a compliment?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Defeat the "answer" to complete my challenge.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Very well. Not many can spot the difference.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Next, you only need to defeat the "answer".

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: A splendid display. I have underestimated you.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Go. The "answer" is right ahead.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: A pity. You did not understand my message.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: My my. Are you uncultured, or purely daft?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Are you still lost? Yet truth is one and only.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: It's a shame. Though your determination does pique my interest.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Very well... We shall consider this done.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: You have passed my first test.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: In front of you is the guardian of the courtyard.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Defeat it to prove your strength.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: A less than satisfactory performance, but, you pass.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Make your way through. Qu is at the top of the tower.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: How unexpected. Truly amazing. Should we have a chat, good people from Babylonia?

Name: Lee
Text: Who are you? I don't feel any hostility from you.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: I am hostile, though perhaps not as much as the others. I'm a member of the Kowloong Crew, after all.

Name: Liv
Text: Kowloong Crew... What's your relationship with those on the Nighter...?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: They replicated our system. On the Nighter, they have nine members.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: But right here in Kowloong, we have nine crews.

Name: Ayla
Text: So... Nine special departments in the city?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: You can say that. Plus, not all of us are involved in such reckless warfare.

Name: Lee
Text: So, not everyone's supporting Qu?

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: She's only a vessel of the will of the majority. And she knows that.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: Anyway, consider this a little nice gesture. I shall waste no more of your time.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: The door is now open. Qu is at the top of the tower. You can go ahead.

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: (First Gabriel, and now Gray Raven.)

Name: Yazi (?)
Text: (I'm afraid this planet isn't going your way, Qu.)

Name: α
Text: Automatons from Murmansk? Modded to withstand the virus?

Name: α
Text: I thought you'd bring something to wow me, but... Whatever.

Name: Rosetta
Text: All arctic machines, take on a defensive formation!

Name: α
Text: Hah, finally, something new...

Name: α
Text: Not coming by yourself? Heh. Guess I'll play with your little pets first.

Name: α
Text: Let's see how long your little toys can keep up.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Fierce as always... But you won't get past me!

Name: Luna
Text: Something isn't right here, sister.

Name: α
Text: ...Buying time, aren't you, Rosetta?

Name: Rosetta
Text: Took you long enough to figure that out.

Name: Rosetta
Text: I won't let you pass...!

Name: Kamui
Text: Come back here!

Name: Chrome
Text: What's happening? Kamui.

Name: Kamui
Text: A few weird mechanoids were carrying something and sneaking around. They ran off the second they saw me!

Name: Kamui
Text: Then I was intercepted by Musashi IX!

Name: Chrome
Text: Musashi IX...? Why is it here?

Name: Chrome
Text: I've never seen this mechanoid. No corruption signal detected... Kamui, what's your status?

Name: Kamui
Text: Tch, we lost sight of it!

Name: Chrome
Text: Kamui, send the image data of that strange mechanoid you met to me.

Name: Kamui
Text: You got it!

Name: Kamui
Text: What's that noise... I'll go check!

Name: Chrome
Text: Come back! I need to upload the image data to the system terminal for further analysis...

Name: Kamui
Text: There you are!

Name: Chrome
Text: Stay there and wait for me. Don't do anything rash.

Name: Kamui
Text: Leader! Leader! I'm here!

Name: Kamui
Text: Huh... This is...?

Name: Liv
Text: The connection seems to be going well...

Name: Lee
Text: Hope it stays that way...

Name: Lucia
Text: Wait, what's this...

Name: Lee
Text: Dammit, it's a defensive data tide!

Name: Lucia
Text: No matter what went through, we'll have to go through this if we want to find it.

Name: Lucia
Text: Phew... It's finally gone.

Name: Lee
Text: The signal trails back to the main elevator... We'll have to go back and keep searching...

Name: Bianca
Text: Luckily I've made it in time...

Name: Bianca
Text: If those Defense Programs activated the alarm, we'll be facing a lot more of them.

Name: Lucia
Text: Bianca! Why are you...

Name: Bianca
Text: It's a long story. I have my mission too.

Name: Bianca
Text: But now that we're heading the same way, let's stick together.

Name: Bianca
Text: There are some Defense Programs patrolling this area... Let's get rid of them before they raise the alarm.

Name: Lucia
Text: Are they trying to protect something?

Name: Bianca
Text: From their patrol pattern, I don't see anything worth our attention. Maybe we'll find some clues in this area.

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's search around then.

Name: Bianca
Text: No luck here. We'll have to...

Name: Lee
Text: Are you really "Bianca"?

Name: Liv
Text: This virtual space feels so real... Even the guide looks exactly like what we have in Babylonia.

Name: Liv
Text: Ah, look, Lucia! That's the shop I told you the other day!

Name: Lucia
Text: That boutique you mentioned? Let's go together after this mission.

Name: Lee
Text: Error: Illegal intrusion by external data entities detected.

Name: Lucia
Text: Is that us?

Name: Lee
Text: No. We came using Babylonia's link.

Name: Lee
Text: Could it be...?

Name: Lucia
Text: What?

Name: Lee
Text: Nothing. I don't have enough evidence yet.

Name: Lucia
Text: Today's special: synthetic latte with hazelnut syrup—buy two get one free!

Name: Liv
Text: A cafe...?

Name: Lee
Text: What's the point of investigating a place like this...

Name: Bianca
Text: Hmm? What's up?

Name: Bianca
Text: Leave the ground floor to me. You can search the upper one.

Name: Bianca
Text: Hmm? What's up?

Name: Lucia
Text: Is this a... security barrier?

Name: Lee
Text: Watch out! There's more from behind!

Name: Defense Program
Text: Threat detected in the area. Activating extermination mode.

Name: Lucia
Text: No!

Name: Bianca
Text: Move back!

Name: Liv
Text: What's this?!

Name: Lucia
Text: I got you.

Name: Bianca
Text: Target hostile. Engaging defense mode.

Name: Lee
Text: Dammit. She's hijacked the Defense Programs.

Name: Lucia
Text: We just have to get rid of them then.

Name: Lee
Text: ...She's even hijacked the security barrier module.

Name: Liv
Text: The port to deactivate it is on the other side... We can't do anything from here.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...We have to find another way.

Name: Defense Program
Text: More threats detected in the area. Activating extermination mode.

Name: Lee
Text: That "Bianca" has made too many bridging attempts. All Defense Programs in the region are now alerted.

Name: Lee
Text: We can't get away without fighting.

Name: Defense Program
Text: More threats detected in the area. Activating extermination mode.

Name: Liv
Text: Her last signal... is just up ahead!

Name: Lee
Text: ...Guess we have to go through them.

Name: Lee
Text: A hidden channel, as I thought.

Name: Liv
Text: According to my scan, the destination of her bridging connection... is right there.

Name: Lee
Text: The billboards look a bit strange... Is that also a result of bridging?

Name: Liv
Text: Indeed. I can probably estimate her jump locations and routes using that.

Name: Guide
Text: In N.E. 2130, Dominik the Great Hero submitted a proposal as the Chief Technology Officer of the Science Council.

Name: Guide
Text: One after another, global organizations signed the "Earth Book" protocol and connected to "Gestalt", a public service system.

Name: Guide
Text: For the first time ever, humankind was able to unite completely under the most urgent global topic: space colonization.

Name: Lee
Text: Dominik...

Name: Liv
Text: Where would he be now...? Is he still alive?

Name: Lucia
Text: I don't know. He is still marked as "missing in action" in the database.

Name: Lucia
Text: There's a stone monument in front of the parliament. I feel like it carries many stories.

Name: Lee
Text: I read about it. It's the Monument of Unity.

Name: Lee
Text: The shattered pieces represent people separated by borders. They now rejoin one another to form a complete cube named "World"...

Name: Lee
Text: ...That's what the book said.

Name: Liv
Text: Lee really knows a lot.

Name: Lee
Text: ...The history books about the Golden Age were placed in a very obvious section in the library, that's all.

Name: Lucia
Text: The parliament building is huge... There are no undamaged buildings of this scale on the surface anymore.

Name: Liv
Text: If we can take back the Earth, there will be buildings like this.

Name: Liv
Text: I'm sure Karenina would love to build something bigger than it.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Yeah.

Name: Lee
Text: The culprit is right behind this door...

Name: Huaxu
Text: Calculation result: A battle with you is inevitable.

Name: Huaxu
Text: You cannot interrupt Huaxu's plan.

Name: Huaxu
Text: Operation... disrupted... Unable to recover connection... with the root server...

Name: Huaxu
Text: R-r-r-reconnecting... F-f-failed...

Name: Lucia
Text: Too many Corrupted here. We can't avoid a fight if we want to set up the security terminal.

Name: Lucia
Text: We will make sure Lee is safe. I'll leave the rest to you.

Name: Lee
Text: I got this.

Name: Bridget
Text: I suggest installing a backup security terminal.

Name: Bridget
Text: Better safe than sorry.

Name: Lucia
Text: This is the last area to investigate.

Name: Liv
Text: Hope we can find a clue...

Name: Liv
Text: Something's wrong with this Corrupted.

Name: Lee
Text: Let's knock it out first!

Name: Murol
Text: The rest have been drawn off. We've just got this Riot left, right?

Name: Lucia
Text: Affirmative. Take down the Riot model before Hiro comes back, then sweep and clear all Corrupted elements.

Name: Xun
Text: Five-by-five! Let's go, Murol!

Name: Murol
Text: Go right, I'll go left!

Name: Xun
Text: Got it! What a naughty thing.

Name: Murol
Text: Hurry and finish it off, Lucia.

Name: Murol
Text: We can't move while holding it here. The enemy can easily target us!

Name: Former Commandant
Text: Lucia, strike the final blow.

Name: Lucia
Text: Understood.

Name: Murol
Text: Hold up, how is this thing still moving?!

Name: Xun
Text: Must be the Punishing Virus.

Name: Xun
Text: Records indicate that the virus has rewritten and repaired its hosts before.

Name: Lucia
Text: Which also means that our attacks are working. Keep up the good work.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...I'll send you to your end!

Name: Lucia
Text: Who's there?! Murol! Xun!!

Name: Xun
Text: My Inver-Device... Dammit, Riot is going to... break free...

Name: Murol
Text: Be careful... facing Riot alone...

Name: Lucia
Text: I see... All I remembered was the electronic shackle on Riot had somehow disappeared.

Name: Lucia
Text: I didn't know I was the only one left.

Name: Lucia
Text: But that's okay. I will take on it by myself, just like what I did last time!

Name: Liv
Text: No, Lucia. You have us now!

Name: Lee
Text: Can't maximize the efficiency if you fight alone while there are teammates around.

Name: Lucia
Text: Thank you...

Name: Lucia
Text: I don't have to fight alone anymore.

Name: Lucia
Text: Nothing can break Gray Raven apart!

Name: Kamui
Text: They said it requires more investigation, but will the Red Tide really be in such places?

Name: Kamui
Text: At any rate, there are only scorched earth and ashes left.

Name: Wanshi
Text: But it is true that high concentrations of Punishing Virus can be detected occasionally.

Name: Wanshi
Text: I'll set up the detection device while you go and check the situation below.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Let me know if you find anything.

Name: Kamui
Text: Isn't this the core strike zone of the Longinus Arsenal?

Name: Kamui
Text: Why are there Hetero-Creatures here?!

Name: Wanshi
Text: It seems that the previous detection was not a false positive.

Name: Wanshi
Text: There are some things hidden nearby.

Name: Kamui
Text: These Hetero-Creatures are frailer than before.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Ah, so you've taken care of them as well...

Name: Wanshi
Text: The same is true for upper floor. Some Hetero-Creatures here and there, but it's easily taken are of.

Name: Wanshi
Text: I guess it may be because the Red Tide is declining.

Name: Wanshi
Text: High levels of Punishing Virus can also be detected in the boxes nearby.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Although it may be residue, just to be safe...

Name: Kamui
Text: Let's break them all open and check!

Name: Wanshi
Text: Yes, that's right.

Name: Kamui
Text: Wanna bet and see who finds more hidden Hetero-Creatures?

Name: Wanshi
Text: Why would I do something like that…

Name: Wanshi
Text: But I'll come to your aid if you're in trouble.

Name: Kamui
Text: Deal!

Name: Kamui
Text: Wait, that sounded from above.

Name: Kamui
Text: Is there a new batch Hetero-Creatures?

Name: Kamui
Text: Let's go check it out!

Name: Kamui
Text: Ugh, there's more!

Name: Wanshi
Text: They don't seem to have been lurking here all the time.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Maybe they came from somewhere else?

Name: Kamui
Text: Not too many enemies left, let's get it over with.

Name: Kamui
Text: What are these?!

Name: Wanshi
Text: A new variety.

Name: Wanshi
Text: There's not a lot of them. Maybe they got separated or only they survived?

Name: Kamui
Text: This area has been cleared.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Well, the Punishing concentration was also detected to be abnormal.

Name: Kamui
Text: OK, let's call Capt over.

Name: Kamui
Text: This area has been cleared.

Name: Kamui
Text: Wanshi, how's it going over there?

Name: Kamui
Text: Hmm? Are you still dealing with those detection device?

Name: Kamui
Text: Let's go and check on him!

Name: Kamui
Text: Wanshi! I did it!

Name: Wanshi
Text: I see. I'll come over to help.

Name: Kamui
Text: All the boxes are checked!

Name: Wanshi
Text: There's not too many, you can handle it yourself.

Name: Wanshi
Text: I'll continue to install the detection device, so I'll leave the guarding to you.

Name: Kamui
Text: Mission cleared! Looks like we finished at the same time!

Name: Wanshi
Text: The Hetero-Creatures haven't given up attacking yet, let's move together.

Name: Wanshi
Text: I knew there were still some here.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Looks like I was right.

Name: Wanshi
Text: It's weak, and the Longinus Arsenal did a toll on it.

Name: Wanshi
Text: These Hetero-Creatures have mastered many skills only seen in animals and insects, such as hiding.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Only residue left here.

Name: Wanshi
Text: Punishing concentration also has the possibility of false positives.

Name: Wanshi
Text: No news is good news.

Name: Wanshi
Text: ...There's nothing inside.

Name: Kamui
Text: There really are Hetero-Creatures hiding here!

Name: Kamui
Text: What exactly did you do to avoid the Longinus Arsenal?

Name: Kamui
Text: I found another one!

Name: Kamui
Text: Did you just come out and hide here?

Name: Kamui
Text: Nothing!

Name: Kamui
Text: Is it a good news that no Hetero-Creatures have been found?

Name: Kamui
Text: How's everything going over there, Wanshi?

Name: Camu
Text: I just came up from below.

Name: Camu
Text: The Red Tide over there is not enough to flood the whole underground waterway.

Name: Camu
Text: But you don't need so many Red Tides to kill Constructs.

Name: Camu
Text: Get out of here. Even if it isn't flooded, the concentration of Punishing here is high enough to make us Corrupted.

Name: Chrome
Text: There are intercepted Hetero-Creatures everywhere.

Name: Camu
Text: Fall back while fighting.

Name: Camu
Text: You are... not only injured, but also Corrupted.

Name: Camu
Text: I wish Wanshi were here.

Name: Camu
Text: Damn, there's not even time for repairs.

Name: Chrome
Text: The concentration of Punishing is still rising.

Name: Camu
Text: You better stay away from me, too, or you'll get worse.

Name: Camu
Text: There you go again.

Name: Chrome
Text: Looks like a switch connecting the gate.

Name: Camu
Text: If the Red Tide wants to pass, this kind of thing can't stop it.

Name: Chrome
Text: It is enough to buy us some time.

Name: Chrome
Text: The concentration of Punishing behind us is very high, so there's no need to turn back.

Name: Camu
Text: Tsk... I thought you were so severely Corrupted that you couldn't tell the direction.

Name: Chrome
Text: It looks like a passage behind the door, but it's locked.

Name: Camu
Text: Nothing a bit of violence can't solve.

Name: Chrome
Text: No, this place has been in disrepair for a long time, and damage may cause it to collapse.

Name: Chrome
Text: But this lock is very old, and it can be opened if we have the key.

Name: Camu
Text: Well, let's look for it then.

Name: Chrome
Text: The door opened.

Name: Camu
Text: Looks like a shortcut.

Name: Chrome
Text: I got the key, it should open the door from earlier.

Name: Chrome
Text: We're very close to the upper floor.

Name: Chrome
Text: The Red Tide is about to flood here.

Name: Chrome
Text: Hurry up, go up the ladder to the upper floor.

Name: Camu
Text: No, you go first.

Name: Camu
Text: Don't you hear that? A mass of Hetero-Creatures are coming.

Name: Camu
Text: One of us should be left behind to take care of it.

Name: Camu
Text: If these get through, none of us will be able to get out.

Name: Chrome
Text: Camu...

Name: Chrome
Text: Take care, meet us soon!

Name: Chrome
Text: This valve seems to be used to divert water channels. What should I do?

Name: Chrome
Text: It seems to be a locked door to a shortcut. What should I do?

Name: Chrome
Text: I found a dusty key, what should I do?

Name: Chrome
Text: The equipment over there seems to be used to divert the waterway. What should I do?

Name: Vera
Text: Blocking the red tide, while looking for her. That's what we are here to do.

Name: Noctis
Text: It seems you are the closest to the control room!

Name: Noctis
Text: If you want a clue, knock on the old console over there.

Name: No. 21
Text: I think we should deal with the Red Tide first.

Name: No. 21
Text: But when the valve is blocked, these Hetero-Creatures will get mad.

Name: Vera
Text: The valve is right here. Get rid of it first.

Name: Vera
Text: The Red Tide leaked? Did they come from other unblocked places?

Name: Vera
Text: Although the current Inver-Device has been enhanced, it is still fatal to be drenched by it.

Name: Vera
Text: I need something to stop it.

Name: Vera
Text: Let's pass like this first.

Name: Vera
Text: But... what's the sound?

Name: Vera
Text: It's nothing new.

Name: No. 21
Text: Some Hetero-Creatures are heading toward you.

Name: Vera
Text: How troublesome.

Name: No. 21
Text: ...Hello, hello, are you still alive?
Aahhhhh!

Name: Vera
Text: What's going on?

Name: No. 21
Text: I found a Construct entangled by Hetero-Creatures.

Name: No. 21
Text: It's alive.

Name: Vera
Text: Well, they're safe now so just leave them there.

Name: Vera
Text: It's not that we can't manage, but we have to go to the control room first.

Name: Vera
Text: I'm here.

Name: Noctis
Text: I hope you can find clues on that rusty machine, bless you!

Name: Vera
Text: Shut up.

Name: Vera
Text: ...Endless troubles.

Name: No. 21
Text: I'm trying to seal off the Red Tide leaks and install the Polyfurnace.

Name: Vera
Text: OK, I'll go back and screw on those valves.

Name: No. 21
Text: The flow rate is reduced, Capt. Go on next valve.

Name: Vera
Text: It seems that there is no information here except trouble.

Name: Vera
Text: What's going on at your side?

Name: Noctis
Text: Not much different! Let's check once more and then go back. I don't want to be swallowed up by trouble.

Name: Vera
Text: There are more floors here. You can't leave until all of them are carefully checked.

Name: Noctis
Text: Huh? Why?!

Name: Vera
Text: What about No. 21?

Name: No. 21
Text: I'm still trying to seal off the Red Tide leaks and install the Polyfurnace.

Name: Vera
Text: Finish our original tasks and then meet at the exit.

Name: Vera
Text: The valve in the piston area can be opened first. What should I do?

Name: System Voice
Text: All communication to Kamui and Wanshi of Strike Hawk have been disconnected.

Name: System Voice
Text: All connections to the Gray Raven Commandant have been disconnected.

Name: Chrome
Text: ...Sign of the deviation... of M.I.N.D...

Name: Chrome
Text: ...Need to... return...

Name: Chrome
Text: No, those three fighting the Agent require Commandant's help more than I do, not to mention that...

Name: Chrome
Text: ...I must hold on for now.

Name: Chrome
Text: I can control...

Name: Chrome
Text: ...They... are still waiting for me.

Name: Hetero-Hive Mother
Text: ... Hush now, little baby...

Name: Chrome
Text: Is it singing?

Name: Hetero-Hive Mother
Text: ...Kana... My Kana...

Name: Hetero-Hive Mother
Text: Mom will always, always love you...

Name: Chrome
Text: What was that...

Name: Cinderelik
Text: ... Don't hurt my mom...

Name: Chrome
Text: Is she really your mother?

Name: Cinderelik
Text: Yes... She has my mom's human data.

Name: Cinderelik
Text: Although the data are incomplete...

Name: Chrome
Text: Human Data? I remembered it's a tech in Golden Age.

Name: Cinderelik
Text: Yes, it's an AI generated from one's data.

Name: Cinderelik
Text: People use it to... remember the dead.

Name: Chrome
Text: What's your purpose? Do you believe this will bring her back to life?

Name: Chrome
Text: Even if you "made" it, it is not your original mother.

Name: Cinderelik
Text: But that's enough.

Name: Cinderelik
Text: I have been... looking for her...

Name: Chrome
Text: What you are looking for is just a collection of the concept of "Mother".

Name: Cinderelik
Text: But that's enough... Please... Don't take her away...

Name: Chrome
Text: ...I'm sorry.

Name: Chrome
Text: I also have a position that I must protect.

Name: Vera
Text: Get out of my way!

Name: Vera
Text: We're almost at the top, come on!

Name: Memo Fragment 1
Text: (I often had to go over the mountains when I served in the outpost. <color=#ff7f00>The twin brothers</color> were always there with me.)

Name: Memo Fragment 2
Text: (Even now, I still keep them next to my <color=#ff7f00>sleeping cabin</color>. They are the proof that I was once a soldier.)

Name: Memo Fragment 3
Text: (I bought a cookbook. Shouldn't be too hard to learn <color=#ff7f00>three dishes</color> in three months, right?)

Name: Memo Fragment 4
Text: (I should search the <color=#ff7f00>bookshelf</color> during work breaks. Maybe one day I'll become a chef like Merry...)

Name: Memo Fragment 5
Text: (My daughter and wife are going out today. I just remember that I have a <color=#ff7f00>family photo</color> here.)

Name: Memo Fragment 6
Text: (We took it 3 years ago on Mt. Morotori. I've been keeping it up above the <color=#ff7f00>balcony</color>. My daughter's smile can cure all my wounds.)

Name: Memo Fragment 7
Text: (Since I signed for the navigator test, I must study hard for it. I always have problem remembering the <color=#ff7f00>Big Four Principles</color> though.)

Name: Memo Fragment 8
Text: (Anyway, I'm ready. First, let me revise once every day using the <color=#ff7f00>hand-held terminal</color>.)

Name: Memo Fragment 9
Text: (Oreco is full of <color=#ff7f00>straight lines</color>. No way I'll lose to West on this!)

Name: Memo Fragment 10
Text: (Let me prove that the <color=#ff7f00>Dodge Van</color> will rule Oreco!)

Name: Rosetta
Text: While you were using the terminal, we scanned all the nearby objects that could be related.

Name: Rosetta
Text: I have marked some potential areas of concern.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Go to those places, and you may find clues that lead to the next step.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Commandant, it's up to you to decide.

Name: Rosetta
Text: The memo mentioned "twin brothers."

Name: Rosetta
Text: It must be pointing at the snow boots in the sleeping cabin.

Name: Rosetta
Text: The "three dishes" mentioned in the memo can be found in one of the books.

Name: Rosetta
Text: It's pointing at the bookshelf to the southeast of the lab.

Name: Rosetta
Text: The keyword is "family photo." If that photo is nearby, it should be fairly easy to find.

Name: Rosetta
Text: The tips are now displayed.

Name: Rosetta
Text: The "Big Four Principles" can be found in a hand-held terminal.

Name: Rosetta
Text: There are many terminals here, but the correct one has already been marked.

Name: Rosetta
Text: The memo mentioned "straight lines" and other similar terms. It should be related to vehicles.

Name: Rosetta
Text: This is probably it.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Based on the tip, this password is related to a card game called "five-card stud."

Name: Rosetta
Text: Try again. Be cautious.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Give it a try once you have enough passwords.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Hmm, this should work.

Name: Rosetta
Text: If my guess is right, this should unlock it.

Name: Rosetta
Text: Something is wrong with this password.

Name: Rosetta
Text: I reserve my opinion on this password combination.

Name: Diana
Text: This hole leads directly to the underground...

Name: Rosetta
Text: Let's just keep moving.

Name: Rosetta

Text: Are humans supposed to hibernate until the machines have a result?

Name: Old Man
Text: Ludicrous... What an absurd plan coming from the leaders of our School!

Name: Director
Text: I hate to say this, but given the situation, this is probably the only way.

Name: Archive Terminal
Text: School Archive — 19299/10

Name: Man
Text: Is the Chairman really going to give the go ahead?

Name: Director
Text: Does he have a choice? Look at what happened on the surface.

Name: Director
Text: Even if the disaster ends, we will still be the only humans he can have an influence on.

Name: Woman
Text: What a plan. A war between machines of equal numbers and strength, determined only through self-evolution?

Name: Man
Text: ...There aren't many of us left. At least this is better than wasting lives in meaningless infighting.

Name: Askr
Text: To. End everything. Must find. "The Strip of Truth".

Name: Askr
Text: It's. A place. I know. Where.

Name: Askr
Text: But. Embla. Has problem. Cannot. Get there.

Name: Liv
Text: Let me take a look.

Name: Liv
Text: I've made some emergency repairs on Embla's action module. This should help her move for now.

Name: Liv
Text: But she won't be able to fight unless I replace the entire module.

Name: Lee
Text: I remember there are some fallen mechanoids outside... We can probably make use of them.

Name: Lee
Text: More mechanoids are moving again?

Name: Mechanoid
Text: Purpose is meaningless now. Activating indiscriminate attack mode.

Name: Lucia
Text: Askr, Embla, stay back. We will take down the mechanoids!

Name: Lee
Text: The damaged mechanoids are moving again... Will this keep happening as we move forward?

Name: Liv
Text: I see another fallen mechanoid over there... Looks like its action module is still intact.

Name: Lucia
Text: Start the repairs, Liv.

Name: Liv
Text: Alright.

Name: Lee
Text: Wait! More motion signals nearby!

Name: System
Text: Tip 17

Name: System
Text: Tip 18

Name: System
Text: Tip 19

Name: System
Text: Tip 20

Name: Archive Terminal
Text: School Archive — 15003/10

Name: Manager
Text: Sir, all the artworks and historical sources in our possession have been transferred to the safehouse as you ordered.

Name: Manager
Text: But Chairman... Are you sure about this?

Name: Old Man
Text: Do it.

Name: Manager
Text: Alright.

Name: Archive Terminal
Text: School Archive — 19445/10

Name: Old Man
Text: Forgive me.

Name: Old Man
Text: For I am about to betray mankind.

Name: Old Man
Text: But this is what we must do.

Name: Old Man
Text: Everything we do is to make the memetics created by humans continue to exist.

Name: Archive Terminal
Text: School Archive — 19345/10

Name: Director
Text: You were looking for me?

Name: Old Man
Text: Yes. There's something I... need to talk to you about.

Name: Director
Text: What is it?

Name: Old Man
Text: I'd like to borrow your life.

Name: Liv
Text: Multiple motion signals detected!

Name: Lucia
Text: Watch out! More damaged mechanoids are moving again!

Name: Askr
Text: I. Can move. Can fight!

Name: Embla
Text: Askr! Askr!

Name: Liv
Text: Askr's signals are getting extremely weak... We need to intervene immediately!

Name: Askr
Text: Embla... P-protect...

Name: Liv
Text: There are tracks everywhere... But I think I know which one belong to Embla.

Name: Liv
Text: ...It's right ahead.

Name: Lee
Text: There are mechanoids around... It won't be an easy trip.

Name: Lucia
Text: Is it just me? I don't see mechanoids with colors anymore.

Name: Liv
Text: ...I've found the next sign.

Name: Liv
Text: There it is.

Name: Liv
Text: Something's... blinking... and glowing...

Name: Lee
Text: Is it a... firefly? I've never seen a real one before.

Name: Lucia
Text: The firefly is flying to the cave where Embla's tracks lead... Could there be something inside?

Name: Lee
Text: Let me see... This is the base of a mechanoid's AI module, with something attached to it. It looks like the core's outer shell.

Name: Liv
Text: This module seems to belong to Askr... But the attachment is in Embla's color...

Name: Lucia
Text: Which means Embla has put some parts of Askr here along with her own parts...

Name: Liv
Text: Did she use them to make some sort of device?

Name: Lee
Text: Possibly. Let me try to activate it.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...It's lighting up.

Name: Liv
Text: ...Reminds me of the "eternal flame" mentioned in the database.

Name: Lucia
Text: Something else seems to be lit up as well.

Name: Lee
Text: Embla stayed here shortly before moving to the plaza outside.

Name: Lee
Text: I just scanned this area with my terrain radar...

Name: Lee
Text: There is a huge cavern underneath the ring... Almost as big as the city above.

Name: Lucia
Text: If Embla was heading out, she must have somehow gone down from the plaza.

Name: Lee
Text: Makes sense. Let's go back.

Name: Sapien Record 01
Text: We will wait for the result inside the cryogenic chamber.

Name: Sapien Record 02
Text: Hidden path ahead. Try &(po — Vann

Name: Sapien Record 03
Text: Don't trust what Vann said.

Name: Sapien Record 04
Text: Wish I can see the blue sky again when I wake up.

Name: Sapien Record 05
Text: I want to be a scientist after I wake up — Jhin

Name: Sapien Record 06
Text: There's something behind you.

Name: Liv
Text: The traces stop here, but Embla is not around.

Name: Lee
Text: The gap of this ring looks a little different. Could it be some sort of elevator-like device?

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's stay here and give it a try then.

Name: Lee
Text: We need to get rid of the mechanoids first.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Better be careful.

Name: Liv
Text: I've found connection signals in the center of the ring. Looks like something will happen if we can stay until its preparation is complete.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Multiple motion signals detected nearby!

Name: Lee
Text: Are they coming to stop us...?

Name: Lucia
Text: Either way, we will have to get rid of them first.

Name: System
Text: Tip 10

Name: System
Text: Tip 11

Name: System
Text: Tip 12

Name: System
Text: Tip 13

Name: System
Text: Tip 14

Name: System
Text: Tip 15

Name: System
Text: Tip 16

Text: Tip 17

Name: System
Text: Tip 18

Name: System
Text: Tip 19

Name: System
Text: Tip 20

Name: Liv
Text: Watch out! The illuminated circles... are releasing high-voltage electric shock!

Name: Lee
Text: Even Constructs would break under that voltage.

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's move to the center while avoiding these areas.

Name: Lee
Text: The signal is interrupted. We need to stay in the center as much as we can.

Name: Lee
Text: I think it's ready now. Finish off the remaining mechanoids.

Name: Machiavelli
Text: War... cannot... continue...

Name: Machiavelli
Text: I... have failed... Father...

Name: Machiavelli
Text: *Emergency exit is now open. You may leave the facility at your convenience.*

Name: System
Text: Tip 4

Name: System
Text: Tip 5

Text: Tip 6

Text: Tip 10

Name: Michael
Text: Michael... wants a game.

Name: Michael
Text: Killing! Is good for health!

Name: Michael
Text: Don't run! Let Big Michael give you a hug!

Name: Michael
Text: I will return...!

Name: Michael
Text: Take this! Michurricane!

Name: Michael
Text: Some blades here! Some blades there! Blades, blades, blades!

Name: Michael
Text: —The sweet torturing is about to begin!

Name: Michael
Text: I once met a guy with a chainsaw installed on his hand. He taught me this move!

Name: Michael
Text: Do you wanna die for a while, or forever?

Name: Michael
Text: Big Michael says hello!

Name: Michael
Text: —The sweet torturing is about to begin!

Name: Michael
Text: Killing! Is good for health!

Name: Lee
Text: Prepare for battle!

Name: Lucia
Text: Wait a second... These Corrupted look strange.

Name: Lee
Text: They're surrounding the throne... as if they're performing a ritual. What are they doing?

Name: Lee
Text: Attempting to capture information about the throne with Spear of F.O.S. for analysis.

Name: Spear of F.O.S.
Text: Capture successful. Filtering valid information—

Name: Lee
Text: Meanwhile, let's keep moving.

Name: Lee
Text: We need to cross the platform to move further inside.

Name: Lucia
Text: I see Constructs... from Babylonia...

Name: Lee
Text: ...Let's retrieve their memory shells to find out what happened.

Name: Lee
Text: Now we should have sufficient data to recreate the projection.

Name: Liv
Text: I wonder what they had been through and seen...

Name: Liv
Text: Watch out, they've noticed us!

Name: Lee
Text: Never thought we could really recover the access history of the control panel...

Name: Murray
Text: I managed to visualize the control panel's past usage. Did it help?

Name: Lee
Text: It did. Good job.

Name: Lucia
Text: That's a projection of... Roland?

Name: Roland
Text: Hmph... I'm about to find out your secret.

Name: Roland
Text: Luna... I'm afraid that...

Name: Lucia
Text: Follow him!

Name: Roland
Text: Biological data that originated from the Punishing Virus? That doesn't seem like Luna's work. Could it be...?

Name: Lee
Text: The road is blocked...

Name: Murray
Text: I got this.

Name: Murray
Text: The blockade all seem to be created using the same method. It's surprisingly easy to crack.

Name: Lee
Text: It's probably a direct adaptation of the blockade program set by the people who built this place. Must be some very old coding.

Name: Liv
Text: Over there...! It's Gabriel!

Name: Gabriel
Text: The Ascension-Network is the only way out...

Name: Gabriel
Text: Grow, for the host of absolute power.

Name: Gabriel
Text: Have you been following me?

Name: Roland
Text: Will you believe me if I say I'm just passing by?

Name: Gabriel
Text: Obviously not.

Name: Roland
Text: You've been working on some new toy recently, right? Can I take a look?

Name: Gabriel
Text: ...Enough said.

Name: Gabriel
Text: Prove your loyalty to the Ascension-Network first.

Name: Roland
Text: Wait, wait! Why are you attacking me already?!
Intruder detected. Activating defense protocol—

Name: Roland
Text: Well, it's time for you...

Name: Roland
Text: ...To show me how much you have grown.

Name: Roland
Text: Is that all? Don't disappoint your old friend.

Name: Roland
Text: (Chuckles) Not bad.

Name: Roland
Text: Hmm, I see... It's about time.

Name: Gabriel
Text: I have prepared a little trial for you. Please, prove your loyalty to the Ascension-Network.

Name: Luna
Text: Gabriel... You'll pay for your foolishness.

Name: Gabriel
Text: Please.

Name: Luna
Text: ...What lowly creations.

Name: Luna
Text: ...Is that all you got?

Name: Gabriel
Text: Magnificent. No wonder the Ascension-Network chose you as the agent.

Name: Gabriel
Text: This overwhelming power of yours... Show me more of it.

Name: Luna
Text: If this is all you have...

Name: Gabriel
Text: I would like to be your opponent, if I may.

Name: Tutorial
Text: Time for some battle revision.

Name: Tutorial
Text: First, use <color=#FF0000>3-Ping</color> to accumulate Annihilation Pts.

Name: Tutorial
Text: When you have sufficient Annihilation Pts, press and hold <color=#FF0000>Basic Attack</color> to enter the <color=#FF0000>Annihilation State</color>.

Name: Tutorial
Text: Now crush these insects!

Name: Tutorial
Text: Under the Annihilation State, you can use special <color=#FF0000>Annihilation Orbs</color>, as well as enhanced Basic Attacks which will cost Annihilation Pts.

Name: Tutorial
Text: After every <color=#FF0000>3-Ping</color>, the next Orb pinged is regarded as a <color=#FF0000>3-Ping</color>.

Name: Lucia
Text: Alpha has chosen to do it this way...

Name: Lucia
Text: Probably because she still has some regrets.

Name: α
Text: Even after becoming an Ascendant, I was still searching for them.

Name: α
Text: But... The promised recall was but a lie.

Name: Lucia
Text: Murol and Xun...

Name: α
Text: The Gray Ravens you believe in would end up just like them...

Name: Ravenge
Text: Why can't you just die?

Name: Hiro
Text: Lucia... Go. You can make it on your own...

Name: α
Text: Even if you can move on from your memories, things like this will happen again.

Name: Luna?
Text: Lucia? Are you also going to leave me?

Name: Lucia
Text: Luna.

Name: Lucia
Text: My promise to you won't change even after I leave this place.

Name: Lucia
Text: Please, give me a little more time. I will find a way.

Name: Lucia
Text: A way to really hold those hands of yours.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Are you "me" before the divergence point? Why are you here?

Name: Lucia
Text: Because you have completely accepted me.

Name: Lucia
Text: Come, "me" in the future. Let me lend you a hand.

Name: Lucia
Text: This is your reward for facing your past.

Name: Lucia
Text: Sorry, Luna. I know you are only an illusion of the M.I.N.D.

Name: Lucia
Text: I must go. I can't change anything staying here.

Name: Luna?
Text: Lucia... Don't...

Name: Luna
Text: Even if I have to resort to violence...

Name: Luna
Text: I must keep you here...

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Are you "me" before the divergence point? Why are you here?

Name: Lucia
Text: Because you have completely accepted me.

Name: Lucia
Text: Come, "me" in the future. Let me lend you a hand.

Name: Lucia
Text: This is your reward for facing your past.

Name: Lucia
Text: No, this time... I still choose to protect you.

Name: Luna
Text: Lucia... Don't go...

Name: Lucia
Text: According to the coordinates, the entrance should be nearby...

Name: Lee
Text: Be careful, there are Corrupted nearyby.

Name: Lucia
Text: This place doesn't look like any industrial or residential area. Why would there be Corrupted...?

Name: Lee
Text: No idea, but we better get rid of them if we want to explore this place.

Name: Lee
Text: Strange mechanoids.

Name: Mechanoid
Text: Defect, defect.

Name: Lucia
Text: Were those Corrupted coming after them?

Name: Lee
Text: Hmm? There's something nearby.

Name: Lee
Text: Better search with caution.

Name: Lee
Text: Better search with caution.

Name: Lucia
Text: Phew...

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's keep moving and find where the mechanoids came from.

Name: Lucia
Text: If those strange mechanoids came from the facility, we should be able to find the entrance by going back the same route.

Name: Lee
Text: All I see are rubbles and debris...

Name: Liv
Text: There are sounds and motion signals... from the cave's entrance!

Name: Lucia
Text: Over there!

Name: Liv
Text: How strange that they kept mumbling something about "defect"...

Name: Lucia
Text: Let move toward where they came from.

Name: Lucia
Text: Is that a... door?

Name: Lee
Text: Looks like so.

Name: Lee
Text: There is a huge area behind the door.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...So this may probably be the entrance to the facility.

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's keep going then.

Name: Unknown
Text: Tap to use POD Skill: Sword

Name: Lucia
Text: The gate ahead... is locked.

Name: Lee
Text: ...How come there are Jitterbombs around?

Name: Liv
Text: Maybe they came from the surface and accidentally ended up here?

Name: Lucia
Text: A closed gate... Jitterbombs... I have a plan.

Name: Lucia
Text: What if we lure the Jitterbombs to the gate and detonate them...?

Name: Lee
Text: Tsk, too close...

Name: Liv
Text: Good, we can take the Jitterbomb all the way to the gate.

Name: Lee
Text: Almost there. Bring another Jitterbomb and do it again.

Name: Liv
Text: These Jitterbombs seem to be moving in a pattern.

Name: Liv
Text: If that's the case, I can try to make a bait from those remains...

Name: Liv
Text: Great, Commandant, I have successfully lured a Jitterbomb toward the gate.

Name: Lucia
Text: Never thought there would be such a huge city underground...

Name: Liv
Text: But isn't that the sky above us?

Name: Lee
Text: Most likely an artificial sky to provide lighting and comfort.

Name: Controller
Text: Don't stay too long. Remember, you have a mission.

Name: Lucia
Text: You're right. We should be able to enter the city via the gate ahead. Let's go.

Name: Lee
Text: Unlike the mechanoids who claimed to be "defects"... These ones are red.

Name: Liv
Text: And they were not calling themselves "defects" anymore.

Name: Lucia
Text: Let's keep moving. This is probably the right direction.

Name: Red Mechanoid
Text: Destroy! Destroy! Only our faction! Can rule the world!

Name: Blue Mechanoid
Text: Destroy! Destroy! Only our faction! Can rule the world!

Name: Lee
Text: Red mechanoids.

Name: Liv
Text: And blue mechanoids... They are fighting each other.

Name: Lee
Text: If they're fighting, we better stay away.

Name: Lee
Text: Let's refrain from unnecessary fights.

Name: Lucia
Text: Hold on.

Name: Lucia
Text: There's something strange about them...

Name: Liv
Text: Both the red and blue mechanoids... are coming our way!

Name: Lee
Text: Are those mechanoids... attacking another identical mechanoid locked up in a cage?

Name: Lucia
Text: Not quite. That mechanoid isn't red or blue.

Name: Lee
Text: If both the red and blue mechanoids are attacking it, it probably is in a similar situation as us.

Name: Lucia
Text: It's possible. Let's rescue it first.

Name: Lee
Text: Tsk, this cage is pretty hard to break.

Name: Lucia
Text: Watch out, the other mechanoids are coming close!

Name: Lee
Text: ...Give me a break!

Name: Liv
Text: Please don't move. I'll open the cage right away!

Name: Authorization AI
Text: Data record... Authorization ID—Z002003

Name: Authorization AI
Text: School Archive, 1/10.

Name: Old Man
Text: Ladies and gentlemen, today we gather here in order to pursue the destiny of mankind.

Name: Old Man
Text: Zero-point energy, a technology that has never been fully tested and verified, is about to be used on the core components of space colonization.

Name: Old Man
Text: That is a decision beyond mankind... Or, I should say, mankind has expanded beyond its own capabilities.

Name: Old Man
Text: Which means... the only outcome is annihilation.

Name: Authorization AI
Text: School Archive, 3/10.

Name: Woman
Text: How can you make such an important decision sound so inconsequential?!

Name: Old Man
Text: I see... Is this a difficult decision to you all?

Name: Director
Text: ...It's still the first item on the agenda, and they're all gone.

Name: Old Man
Text: One day they will understand the weight of this decision... and why it is necessary.

Name: Lee
Text: Be careful, there's a fight going on in the area ahead.

Name: Lucia
Text: Are they the mechanoids we saw?

Name: Lee
Text: Let's take a look. There isn't any other way if we want to investigate this area further.

Name: Liv
Text: The red and blue forces were fighting, but once they saw us...

Name: Lee
Text: They started attacking us together.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Looks like both the red and blue mechanoids have a similar defense mechanism. Do they see us as a mutual enemy?

Name: Lee
Text: ...Fighting each other while automatically excluding outsiders simultaneously?

Name: Lee
Text: That's worth looking into. Let's keep going and see if there are more similar mechanoids further down the way.

Name: Mechanoid
Text: You. Who are... Y09p[Different. Individual.

Name: Lee
Text: Why did those mechanoids attack you?

Name: Mechanoid
Text: I m-m-m a. Defect. No. Faction. Comrade.

Name: Lucia
Text: Did they attack you because you were not a "comrade"?

Name: Mechanoid
Text: In this "Naraka". Either comrade. Either enemy. Defects and outsiders. Eliminated first.

Name: Lucia
Text: Watch out, the other mechanoids are coming close!

Name: Lee
Text: ...Give me a break!

Name: Luna
Text: I must say, your fortitude has surprised me... But this will not be the end.

Name: Luna
Text: Show me what power means to you, Gabriel.

Name: Gabriel
Text: I am extremely honored to witness your absolute power again.

Name: Gabriel
Text: Miss Luna, this is only the beginning...

Name: Liv
Text: How can we stop a monster of this size...

Name: Lee
Text: Focus on the weak points. The giant body makes them more exposed.

Name: Lucia
Text: Proceed with caution. Don't get hit!

Name: Lee
Text: I have marked the weak points with the Spear of F.O.S. If only we can disable the Polyphage's arms...

Name: Lee
Text: All we need is a couple of minutes to have a shot at getting to the core.

Name: Liv
Text: I will provide support from the rear. You can depend on me!

Name: Lucia
Text: The way forward is clear. Let's go!

Name: Lucia
Text: I was betrayed, but no matter how painful the wounds were, I have decided to always look forward.

Name: Lucia
Text: I will embrace the future with Gray Raven, with Commandant, and everyone in Babylonia.

Name: Lucia
Text: Luna, I want to share my stories with you. Even if there's only darkness ahead of us, I'd like to believe in that tiny spark of hope.

Name: Lucia
Text: ...Because it's a treasure given by those that are important to me, and nothing could replace it.

Name: Lucia
Text: I will cut down anything or anyone that gets in my way!

Name: Lucia
Text: When everything is over... I will gently pat your head like I used to.

Name: Lucia
Text: Sorry, Liv... Lee... But I have made up my mind.

Name: Lucia
Text: I won't let go of those hands again. Those hands who reach out for my help from darkness.

Name: Lucia
Text: Wait, what's this...

Name: Lucia
Text: The contamination rate of Punishing Virus is falling... A new M.I.N.D. connection?

Name: Lucia
Text: This signal... Luna?

Name: Lucia
Text: But connecting with an Ascendant will put too much stress on Commandant. What if...

Name: Lucia
Text: No... I believe in Commandant's decision.

Name: Lucia
Text: I will buy you time before the connection is established... Trust me.

Name: Lucia
Text: Commandant and everyone will be in danger...!

Name: Lucia
Text: I must not... Let this monster reach the surface.

Name: Lucia
Text: I will destroy you right here before I get to Commandant and everyone else!

Name: Lucia
Text: I will never give up!

Name: Lucia
Text: Just... a little longer... Not yet...

Name: Lucia
Text: Ugh...

Name: Luna
Text: Connect to Luna?

Name: Celica
Text: Basic Attack: Launches multiple hits with orbs and spikes.

Name: Celica
Text: The Basic Attack combo will be varied if you <color=#ee7d7c>quickly follow up with a Basic Attack after a successful dodge</color>.

Name: Celica
Text: <color=#ee7d7c>After dodging</color>, <color=#ee7d7c>immediately attack</color> to cast the 3rd hit of Basic Attack directly.

Name: Celica
Text: Red Orb: Launches spheres forward to bombard the enemy for Physical DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: Blue Orb: Casts a virus network that moves with the target or self for 3s, dealing multiple hits of Physical DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: Yellow Orb: Channels energy flow underground to cast up to 4 piercing attacks at the target's location, dealing Physical DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: Signature Move: Alters the gravity within a large area forward, dealing massive Dark DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: Red Orb <color=#ee7d7c>3-Ping</color>: Hurls the spheres floating behind Luna forward, randomly attacking targets and dealing Dark DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: After a 3-Ping, <color=#ee7d7c>any Orb pinged</color> will also be regarded as a 3-Ping.

Name: Celica
Text: Now the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation Pts</color> are full, <color=#ee7d7c>press and hold the Attack button</color> to enter the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color> and deal Dark DMG to nearby targets.

Name: Celica
Text: Under the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color>, Luna gains new Basic Attack combos.

Name: Celica
Text: Every <color=#ee7d7c>Basic Attack</color> will get you <color=#ee7d7c>1</color> point. Once there are <color=#ee7d7c>4</color> points, special Red Orbs are activated. Tap the activated special Red Orb to cast <color=#ffda58>Shattered Crown</color>.

Name: Celica
Text: Tap unactivated Red Orbs to cast <color=#ffda58>Singularity</color> and get <color=#ee7d7c>1</color> point. Cast <color=#ffda58>Shattered Crown</color> again to leave the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color>.

Name: Celica
Text: Blue Orb <color=#ee7d7c>3-Ping</color>: Casts a virus network that moves with the target or self for 3s, dealing multiple hits of Dark DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: Yellow Orb <color=#ee7d7c>3-Ping</color>: Launches up to 3 piercing attacks in front of the target, dealing Dark DMG.

Name: Celica
Text: <color=#ee7d7c>Press and hold the Attack button</color> to enter the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color>, then cast Basic Attacks or <color=#ffda58>Singularity</color> 4 times to activate special Red Orb, the <color=#ffda58>Shattered Crown</color>.

Name: Celica
Text: <color=#ee7d7c>Press and hold the Attack button</color> to enter the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color>. Under this mode, you can accumulate points by casting Basic Attacks and special Red Orbs, then unleash high burst damage.

Name: Celica
Text: Blue Orb <color=#ee7d7c>3-Ping</color> can also trigger Luna's QTE Skill while she is in the blue slot.

Name: Celica
Text: <color=#ee7d7c>Tap</color> to cast Luna's QTE Skill.

Name: Celica
Text: <color=#ee7d7c>Tap</color> Luna to cast her Entrance Skill

Name: Celica
Text: When Luna enters the battle, she will cast <color=#ee7d7c>Blue Orb 3-Ping</color> to trigger her Core Passive, so any <color=#ee7d7c>Orb pinged next</color> will be regarded as a 3-Ping.

Name: Celica
Text: After every 3-Ping, she gains <color=#ee7d7c>15</color> Annihilation Pts, up to <color=#ee7d7c>60</color>. <color=#ee7d7c>The skill damage of 3-Ping is also converted into Dark DMG</color>.

Name: Celica
Text: After a 3-Ping, <color=#ee7d7c>any Orb pinged</color> will also be regarded as a 3-Ping.

Name: Celica
Text: <color=#ee7d7c>Press and hold the Attack button</color> to enter the <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color>. While Luna is in <color=#ffda58>Annihilation State</color>, she gains up to <color=#ee7d7c>4</color> <color=#ffda58>Annihilation Orbs</color> based on her current <color=#ffda58>Annihilation Pts</color> at the bottom of the screen.

Name: Celica
